<item>
            <title>[LU-17551] &apos;make dpkg-dkms&apos; should not depend on &apos;ed&apos; or &apos;quilt&apos;</title>
                <link>https://jira.whamcloud.com/browse/LU-17551</link>
                <project id="10000" key="LU">Lustre</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;There are a small number of places that use &quot;&lt;tt&gt;ed&lt;/tt&gt;&quot; in &lt;tt&gt;autoMakefile.am&lt;/tt&gt; and &lt;tt&gt;contrib/lbuild/lbuild&lt;/tt&gt; that should be replaced with &lt;tt&gt;sed&lt;/tt&gt; or some other mechanism (&lt;tt&gt;grep -v&lt;/tt&gt;?) to reduce the build dependencies.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Also, &lt;tt&gt;quilt&lt;/tt&gt; is definitely not needed for client builds since this is only used for ldiskfs, and barely needed for server builds.  It is more of a developer tool, and AFAIR the ldiskfs code can still be built without it.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
                <environment></environment>
